      [enso97_colorbar.gif]
      Colors show sea surface height relative to average (for
      example, WHITE= sea level 5 to 12 inches above normal).



             TYPHOON BILIS viewed from
             QUIKSCAT and TRMM

      [TyphoonBilis1.gif]

      Typhoon Bilis, with the same strength as a category 5 hurricane, bore
      down on Taiwan. This composite image from August 21, 2000, show the
      massive storm's most devastating components: rain and wind. Wind was
      measured by Quickscat, rain by TRMM.

      (http://www.jpl.nasa.gov/files/images/captions/bilis1.txt)< /p>
